A recent POLITICO/Morning Consult poll showed Warren with the highest net favorability ratings of the potential VP candidates listed.
Despite the scar tissue from the primary, some Sanders campaign officials said Warren is the most viable progressive in contention for Biden’s vice presidential selection.
“I think one of the things we should do as a progressive movement is, given that he can’t pick Bernie — he said he’s going to pick a woman — we should push for the most progressive woman,” Khanna said.
Sanders’ campaign leadership believes that her assertion that Sanders privately told her a woman couldn’t win, which he denied, hurt him among female voters and amounted to a personal betrayal.
A former aide to Sanders' 2020 campaign added, “Elizabeth Warren has a progressive voting record and progressive ideas and has been a progressive leader.